Step 1: Identify the necessary values from the income statement.  
• Net Profit = -1,175,062.19  
• Total Revenue = 7,099,920.95  

Step 2: Use the formula for Net Profit Margin:  
  Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  

Step 3: Substitute the values into the formula:  
  Net Profit Margin = (-1,175,062.19 / 7,099,920.95) × 100  

Step 4: Calculate the division:  
  -1,175,062.19 / 7,099,920.95 ≈ -0.1655  

Step 5: Multiply by 100 to get a percentage:  
  -0.1655 × 100 ≈ -16.55%  

Thus, the Net Profit Margin is approximately -16.55%.
